# Ops lessons — Breeze Smart Purge

## Project setup (scaffold thread)

- **One repo, one folder:** `C:\Users\kevin\Projects\breeze-smart-purge-plugin` only. Delete ignore `pixelparade-wp-plugin` stub; Cursor sidebar duplicates are old agent sessions, not second projects.
- **Canonical GitHub:** `PixelParade/breeze-smart-purge-plugin` (org). Personal repo is legacy; do not fork workflow across two remotes.
- **Novamira MCP:** project `.cursor/mcp.json` only — never global `~/.cursor/mcp.json`. Hostname must be `breeze-smart-purge.pixelparade.dev` before any MCP call.
- **Do not put plugin code in** `novamira-playground` — that repo is Figma/Bricks command center.
- **Two deploy lanes:** `main` push → staging CI; tag `v*` → GitHub Release zip → MainWP / WP Updates on clients.

## After every deploy or big PHP change

1. `cd public_html && wp plugin list | grep breeze-smart-purge` — parse/fatal errors show here first.
2. Homepage + wp-admin must not show critical-error screen.
3. **Browser check** for UI (admin bar, settings) while logged in.
4. `grep 'Version:' …/breeze-smart-purge.php` on server.

If site is down: **SCP hotfix** to `public_html/wp-content/plugins/breeze-smart-purge/` immediately; do not wait for CI.

## Error logs (staging Cloudways)

| Source | Path / command |
|--------|----------------|
| WP-CLI | `wp plugin list` (fastest) |
| WP debug | `wp-content/debug.log` (only if `WP_DEBUG_LOG`; usually off) |
| Server | `../logs/*error.log`, `php-app*.log` |
| CI | `gh run view <id> --log-failed` |

## Staging deploy (GitHub Actions)

- **User:** `cursor-user` — cannot write `/tmp` or home root; SCP to `public_html/wp-content/plugins/breeze-smart-purge/` only.
- **Master SSH keys** on Cloudways ≠ `cursor-user` keys; CI uses password SCP (`STAGING_SSH_PASSWORD`).
- **Cloudways Git deploy** uses its own SSH key + optional API pull; different from Actions SCP.
- **Novamira MCP** for WP-aware reads; SSH/pscp for bulk file sync.

## GitHub / auth

- `gh auth login --web` when fine-grained PAT lacks org access.
- Authorize PAT for **PixelParade** org; `gh api user/orgs` should list it.
- Never commit `.env.deploy.local`, `.cursor/mcp.json`, or tokens pasted in chat.

## PHP / WordPress pitfalls

- **jQuery in PHP strings:** `$('…')` inside `"…"` → parse error. Use single-quoted PHP strings.
- **Frontend Breeze toolbar:** delegate via `Breeze_Admin::register_admin_bar_menu` (reflection); BSP adds only Smart Purge items. Load `class-wp-screen.php` + `screen.php`; set `WP_Screen::get('front')` before invoke. Never `stdClass` stub (`is_admin()` fatals).
- **Silent try/catch** hid toolbar failure — always verify with WP-CLI or browser after delegate changes.
- **Breeze `load_admin_scripts`** on frontend fatals when `get_current_screen()` is null — enqueue Breeze JS manually on frontend only.

## WP.org submission

- Run **Plugin Check** (`.github/workflows/plugin-check.yml` + `wp plugin check` on staging).
- Release zip must contain only distributable files (`.distignore`); no `.github`, `docs`, `scripts`, dev chunks.
- **GitHub updater** lives in `includes/github-updater.php`; excluded from wp.org zip via `.distignore`; loaded only when `BSP_GITHUB_TOKEN` is in wp-config. GitHub Release zip (`release.yml`) still includes it.
- `readme.txt`: valid UTF-8 (no mojibake), `Tested up to` current WP, `Stable tag` matches header `Version`, `Contributors:` wp.org slugs.
- Plugin Check on staging: `wp plugin install plugin-check --activate` then `wp plugin check breeze-smart-purge --require=wp-content/plugins/plugin-check/cli.php`.
- Full checklist: `docs/WPORG_SUBMISSION.md`.

## Scaffold thread (extra)

- Windows `scp` without PuTTY hangs on password — use `plink`/`pscp` or Novamira MCP `read-file` to pull plugin source.
- `scripts/pull-from-staging.ps1`: tries `pscp`, falls back to plink `cat` + base64.
- Staging plugin is **single-file** (`breeze-smart-purge.php` + `readme.txt`); delete any `includes/` scaffold from initial template unless adding optional files (e.g. github-updater).
- GitHub org repo private → in-plugin updates need `BSP_GITHUB_TOKEN` + release asset `breeze-smart-purge.zip`.
- Cloudways app id `tyaxssmjcp`; remote path `public_html/wp-content/plugins/breeze-smart-purge/`.

